.TH "ubi_notify_all" 9 "ubi_notify_all" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ubi_notify_all \- send a notification to all volumes.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ubi_notify_all
.BI "(struct ubi_device *ubi "  ","
.BI "int ntype "  ","
.BI "struct notifier_block *nb "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ubi" 12
UBI device description object
.IP "ntype" 12
notification type to send (UBI_VOLUME_ADDED, etc)
.IP "nb" 12
the notifier to call
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function walks all volumes of UBI device \fIubi\fP and sends the \fIntype\fP
notification for each volume. If \fInb\fP is NULL, then all registered notifiers
are called, otherwise only the \fInb\fP notifier is called. Returns the number of
sent notifications.
